{
  "answer": "**Śruti** (\"heard\" or revealed) refers to the Vedas, which are regarded as direct divine revelation—eternal, infallible, and the root-source of *Dharma* (sacred law). It holds supreme, unquestioned authority as the embodiment of all knowledge.[^1][^2][^3]\n\n**Smṛti** (\"remembered\"), by contrast, encompasses the traditions, sacred treatises on *Dharma*, conduct of the virtuous, and self-satisfaction derived from or consistent with Śruti. While secondary to Śruti, it signals authority through human sages' recollection and application of Vedic truths, forming a parallel unquestionable source alongside the Vedas themselves. Doubting either renders one an outcast.[^4][^5][^6]\n\nŚruti's authority is primary and absolute (e.g., resolving conflicts or for detached seekers);[^7] Smṛti extends it practically, as the \"sacred tradition\" equal in validity for daily *Dharma* when harmonious with Śruti.[^8]\n\nThe Smṛtis discuss this explicitly in **Manusmṛti 2.6–13** (the foundational exposition in the corpus): the Veda/Śruti is equated with revelation; Smṛti with remembered Dharma-śāstras like Manusmṛti itself.[^9] Yājñavalkya Smṛti 1.3 and 1.7 echo this, listing Smṛti authors (including itself) after Vedas/Purāṇas as *Dharma* sources.[^10]\n\nNo other Smṛti in the corpus (e.g., Pārāśara, Viṣṇu, Nārada) elaborates the distinction as directly.\n\n[^1]: Manusmṛti, Chapter 2, [p-d70b97](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/02/translation/#p-d70b97).\n\n[^2]: Manusmṛti, Chapter 2, [p-76188a](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/02/translation/#p-76188a).\n\n[^3]: Manusmṛti, Chapter 2, [p-4aaac7](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/02/translation/#p-4aaac7).\n\n[^4]: Manusmṛti, Chapter 2, [p-d16075](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/02/translation/#p-d16075).\n\n[^5]: Manusmṛti, Chapter 2, [p-dc0b85](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/02/translation/#p-dc0b85).\n\n[^6]: Manusmṛti, Chapter 2, [p-608b3f](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/02/translation/#p-608b3f).\n\n[^7]: Manusmṛti, Chapter 2, [p-d6ca1b](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/02/translation/#p-d6ca1b).\n\n[^8]: Manusmṛti, Chapter 2, [multi-passage](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/02/translation/#p-d70b97-p-d6ca1b).\n\n[^9]: Manusmṛti, Chapter 2, [full chapter](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/02/translation/).\n\n[^10]: Yājñavalkya Smṛti, Chapter 1, [p-7d795b](/works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/01/translation/#p-7d795b).",
